<paragraph id="E97E36AFFF93FFB4FF3CFD0BFDE5FD0A" blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" box="[151,619,726,751]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
<heading id="B23681C3FF93FFB4FF3CFD0BFDE5FD0A" bold="true" box="[151,619,726,751]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FF3CFD0BFDE5FD0A" authority="Perez, 1890" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1890" box="[151,619,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="flavidus" subSpecies="lutescens">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FF3CFD0BFDE5FD0A" bold="true" box="[151,619,726,751]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FF3CFD0BFE47FD0A" bold="true" box="[151,457,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Bombus flavidus lutescens</emphasis>
(Pérez, 1890)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97E36AFFF93FFB4FF6CFD26FBE0FCD3" blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
It is spread mainly in the Pyrenees (Ornosa &amp; Torres 2009), although there is a quote from the Cantabrian Range (
<bibRefCitation id="8D504B5EFF93FFB4FF46FCC3FEF7FCD2" author="Obeso" box="[237,377,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" refString="Obeso, J. R. (1992) Geographic distribution and community structure of bumblebees in the Northern Iberian Peninsula. Oecologia, 89, 244 - 252." type="journal article" year="1992">Obeso 1992</bibRefCitation>
). It has an orophilous tendency (
<figureCitation id="71FA2A2AFF93FFB4FD4DFCC3FCA4FCD2" box="[742,810,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), between 
<date id="9D7F106FFF93FFB4FC0FFCC2FBC4FCD2" box="[932,1098,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" value="1800" valueMax="2520">
1800 and 
<quantity id="2E399B4AFF93FFB4FBB9FCC3FBC4FCD2" box="[1042,1098,798,823]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.52" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="2520.0">2520</quantity>
</date>
m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1DB6524FF93FFB4FF3CFC9FFA87FC22" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97E36AFFF93FFB4FF3CFC9FFB08FC47" blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
The last samples (
<figureCitation id="71FA2A2AFF93FFB4FECDFC9FFE25FCBE" box="[358,427,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1619,1641]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,1027,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,1020,1596]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing historical locations (●) and recent records (*) of Bombus flavidus lutescens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322692/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) were collected in a wet alpine pasture in a peatland in the upper limit of a fir-pine area with 
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FF64FCBBFEC8FC9A" box="[207,326,870,895]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FF64FCBBFEC8FC9A" box="[207,326,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Abies alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FEFFFCBAFD8CFC9A" box="[340,514,870,895]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FEFFFCBAFD8CFC9A" box="[340,514,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Pinus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FDFCFCBAFC8EFC9B" box="[599,768,871,894]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FDFCFCBAFC8EFC9B" box="[599,768,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Pinus uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with scattered patches of creeping juniper scrub, cranberry and heather, among others, also on 
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FD89FC51FC8CFC46" box="[546,770,906,931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtillus">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FD89FC51FC8CFC46" box="[546,770,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Vaccinium myrtillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC14D2CFF93FFB4FC93FC57FB89FC46" box="[824,1031,906,931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratense">
<emphasis id="DBB5EABDFF93FFB4FC93FC57FB89FC46" box="[824,1031,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Trifolium pratense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity id="2E399B4AFF93FFB4FB81FC56FB0CFC47" box="[1066,1154,907,931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.02" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="2020.0">2020 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
